在[[电子游戏|电子游戏]]-{zh-cn:里;zh-tw:裡;}-，如果[[玩家角色|玩家角色]]失去所有[[生命值|生命值]]，那同时将会失去一次'''生命'''。失去所有生命通常意味着[[游戏结束|游戏结束]]，可能将迫使玩家重新开始游戏 。常见的[[动作游戏|动作类游戏]]中[[玩家角色|玩家角色]]有多次生命，并且还有机会在游戏过程中获得更多。这样玩家就能够挽回在游戏过程中的严重过失。[[電子角色扮演遊戲|角色扮演遊戲]]和[[冒险游戏|冒险游戏]]通常只给予玩家一次生命， 但允许重新加载[[游戏存档|游戏存档]]。<ref name="Adams">{{Cite book|last1 = Ernest|first1 = Adams|date = 2010-04-07|title = Fundamentals of Game Design|url = http://books.google.nl/books?id=-BCrex2U1XMC&dq=checkpoint+warp+game&source=gbs_navlinks_s|publisher = New Riders|page = 161, 168|isbn = 013210475X|accessdate = 2014-12-19|archive-date = 2016-10-11|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161011172642/https://books.google.nl/books?id=-BCrex2U1XMC&dq=checkpoint+warp+game&source=gbs_navlinks_s|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="Fullerton">{{Cite book|last1 = Fullerton|first1 = Tracy|date = 2008-02-08|title = Game Design Workshop: A Playcentric Approach to Creating Innovative Games|url = https://books.google.nl/books?id=OjIYWtqWxtAC&dq=lives+game+design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|publisher = CRC Press|page = 72, 73|isbn = 0240809742|accessdate = 2014-12-19|archive-date = 2020-12-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201213224913/https://books.google.nl/books?id=OjIYWtqWxtAC&dq=lives%20game%20design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|dead-url = no}}</ref> 一次生命可以等同为游戏从开始到结束、任何游戏角色从创建到毁灭的时间。<ref name="gamestyleguide">{{Cite book|last1 = Orlands|first1 = Kyle|last2 = Thomas|first2 = David|last3 = Steinberg|first3 = Scott Matthew|date = 2007|title = The Videogame Style Guide and Reference Manual|url = https://books.google.nl/books?id=E2woAgAAQBAJ&dq=1-up+mushroom&source=gbs_navlinks_s|publisher = Lulu.com|page = 41|isbn = 1430313056|accessdate = 2014-12-10|archive-date = 2020-12-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201213224859/https://books.google.nl/books?id=E2woAgAAQBAJ&dq=1-up%20mushroom&source=gbs_navlinks_s|dead-url = no}}</ref>

== 历史 ==

生命概念可能源于[[彈珠台|彈珠台]]機械街机遊戲的弹珠数量限制。一定量的生命次数(通常是3) 成为了[[街机|街机]]游戏的普遍特点， 与弹珠游戏非常相近，玩家的目标通常是在有限次数的生命下尽可能多的获取积分。<ref name="Rouse">{{Cite book|last1 = Rouse III|first1 = Richard|date = 2010-03-08|title = Game Design: Theory and Practice, Second Edition|url = https://books.google.nl/books?id=tGePP1Nu_P8C&dq=lives+game+design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|publisher = Jones & Bartlett Learning|page = 60|isbn = 1449633455|accessdate = 2014-12-19|archive-date = 2020-12-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201213224918/https://books.google.nl/books?id=tGePP1Nu_P8C&dq=lives%20game%20design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="Lecky">{{Cite book|last1 = Lecky-Thompson|first1 = Guy W.|date = 2008-01-01|title = Video Game Design Revealed|url = https://books.google.nl/books?id=3aQLAAAAQBAJ&dq=lives+game+design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|publisher = Cengage Learning|page = 49|chapter = life|isbn = 1584506075|accessdate = 2014-12-19|archive-date = 2020-12-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201213224911/https://books.google.nl/books?id=3aQLAAAAQBAJ&dq=lives+game+design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|dead-url = no}}</ref>

后来, [[游戏存档|检查点]]或存档允许玩家在失去生命后在一个特殊的游戏进程记录点继续游戏，而不是重新开始。在早期街机游戏中，强化生命值、防御和其他[[属性|属性]]，还有力量升级，使得对于节省角色生命有了更多战略经验并降低对生命值减少所产生的不利影响。<ref name="Lecky">{{Cite book|last1 = Lecky-Thompson|first1 = Guy W.|date = 2008-01-01|title = Video Game Design Revealed|url = https://books.google.nl/books?id=3aQLAAAAQBAJ&dq=lives+game+design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|publisher = Cengage Learning|page = 49|chapter = life|isbn = 1584506075|accessdate = 2014-12-19}}</ref>

== 惯例 ==

包含生命概念的游戏系统会建立一个检查点使得死亡不必要结束游戏，让玩家更加敢于去冒险。多次生命也能让新手玩家有机会在游戏结束前学习到更多的游戏技巧。另外，如果玩家有能力获得额外的生命，系统则会提供附加奖励以激励玩家。<ref name="Rouse">{{Cite book|last1 = Rouse III|first1 = Richard|date = 2010-03-08|title = Game Design: Theory and Practice, Second Edition|url = https://books.google.nl/books?id=tGePP1Nu_P8C&dq=lives+game+design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|publisher = Jones & Bartlett Learning|page = 60|isbn = 1449633455|accessdate = 2014-12-19}}</ref>

然而问题也随之出现。玩家频繁失去生命彻底让玩家失去继续游戏的勇气。若失去一次生命后致使装备、技能或积分也造成损失，那么玩家将更倾向于每次失去生命后就直接重新读取先前的存档。<ref>{{Cite book|last1 = Rogers|first1 = Scott|date = 2014-04-11|title = Level Up! The Guide to Great Video Game Design|url = https://books.google.nl/books?id=2LNaAwAAQBAJ&dq=lives+game+design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|publisher = John Wiley & Sons|page = 300|isbn = 1118877217|accessdate = 2014-12-19|archive-date = 2020-12-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201213224900/https://books.google.nl/books?id=2LNaAwAAQBAJ&dq=lives%20game%20design&hl=nl&source=gbs_navlinks_s|dead-url = no}}</ref>

